	abstract = {With the continuous progress of science and technology, integrating VR technology into mathematics teaching has become an increasingly significant educational trend. This paper mainly studies the application of virtual reality technology in middle school mathematics classrooms and its influence on students' learning. In addition, the Adagrad adaptive learning rate optimization algorithm is introduced to optimize the VR teaching system further. By monitoring students' learning data in real-time, the system can adaptively adjust the difficulty and pace of teaching content. When the system detects that students have difficulty understanding a math concept, Adagrad's algorithm reduces the learning rate of the relevant content, giving students more time and practice to master the concept. Finally, the results show that the Adagrad algorithm can effectively improve the effect of VR teaching systems. © 2025 IEEE.},
